                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d833">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690.419/10–2549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Douglas</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-25T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 25, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3835. Re para 6 DepCirAgam Oct 11, subject export controls for Far East, assume
                    you will seek confirmation Brit agreement selected list 1–B items transmitted
                    for Martin and McIntyre in Deptel 2156 June 22 and confirm to us. Necessary to
                    have agreed list to transmit to other posts as basis for negots.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
